---
/**
 * context-engineering 0006 · Figure 3 — the retrieval × generation 2×2 that names
 * the failing half per quadrant.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source lesson HTML (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the
 * footnote <sup>). Lives as an .astro component so the kebab-case SVG attributes
 * render byte-for-byte (see Fig1's header for the full rationale).
 *
 * This figure references NO arrowhead markers, so it carries no <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 520 280"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A two-by-two of retrieval good or bad against generation faithful or unfaithful, each quadrant naming the diagnosis."
    >
        <text x="260" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >RETRIEVAL &times; GENERATION &mdash; diagnose the failing half</text
        >
        <!-- axis labels -->
        <text x="160" y="40" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >generation faithful</text
        >
        <text x="370" y="40" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >generation unfaithful</text
        >
        <text
            x="44"
            y="110"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#2f5d3a"
            transform="rotate(-90 44 110)">retrieval good</text
        >
        <text
            x="44"
            y="210"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#9a2417"
            transform="rotate(-90 44 210)">retrieval bad</text
        >
        <!-- quadrants -->
        <rect x="64" y="50" width="200" height="100" rx="8" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="164" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >&#10003; correct &amp; grounded</text
        >
        <text x="164" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >ship it; this is the goal</text
        >
        <rect x="272" y="50" width="200" height="100" rx="8" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="372" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >had the context,</text
        >
        <text x="372" y="102" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >ignored it &rarr; hallucination</text
        >
        <text x="372" y="120" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >fix GENERATION (prompt/model)</text
        >
        <rect x="64" y="158" width="200" height="100" rx="8" fill="#fff7e6" stroke="#7a5c00"></rect>
        <text x="164" y="194" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#7a5c00"
            >faithful to junk</text
        >
        <text x="164" y="212" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >grounded but wrong/incomplete</text
        >
        <text x="164" y="228" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >fix RETRIEVAL (recall/context)</text
        >
        <rect x="272" y="158" width="200" height="100" rx="8" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"
        ></rect>
        <text x="372" y="202" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >&#10007; wrong both ways</text
        >
        <text x="372" y="220" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >fix retrieval first, then re-test</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Don't fix the wrong half. A grounded answer over bad context is a <em>retrieval</em> bug; a hallucination
        over good context is a <em>generation</em> bug. The metrics below tell you which quadrant a failing
        case lands in.<sup><a href="#s1" id="r1c">1</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
